See <a href="http://wiki.apache.org/jackrabbit/ConfigurationOverview">http://wiki.apache.org/jackrabbit/ConfigurationOverview</a><br/>
<br/>
&quot;For each workspace that was created, there will also be a workspace.xml file created inside the workspace home directory that will be used for the workspace - these files have to be changed, too, because the workspace-specific configuration inside repository.xml is only used as a template for new workspaces, ie. if you use the createWorkspace of the Jackrabbit API, the workspace.xml is just a copy of the Workspace element inside repository.xml. You can also manually create the workspace folder with a workspace.xml file to create a new workspace yourself (Note that depending on the persistence manager you will also have to setup a database and configure the access to it).&quot;
